The ```getInstance()``` function takes an **_HTML element_** as argument. But you have passed a **_String_**.
Also it needs to be ```bootstrap.Tooltip.getInstance()```.

Example:
```javascript
// Get the element with the Tooltip
const element = document.getElementById('example');

// Get or create Tooltip instance
const tooltip = bootstrap.Tooltip.getOrCreateInstance(element);

// Change content
tooltip.setContent({ '.tooltip-inner': 'New Content' })

// Disable
tooltip.disable();
```
